'''Level 434''', formerly known as '''Level 9.12''', is the 435th level in the Backrooms.
==Description==
{{Blurimage|file=Screenshot 2025-04-26 192345-NEW Level 434-1.png|caption=The main image of '''Level 434'''.}}
'''Level 434''' is an expansive network of suburban developments, houses, and roads. The level closely imitates the "Dreamcore" art style in terms of appearance, with multicolored houses, fine green grass with no weeds, and titular playground structures within parks. The entirety of '''Level 434''' is clean and sterile, with no dirt, mud, or wear and tear present throughout the level as a whole. Any traces of dirt or other residue that did not originate from '''Level 434''' will be cleaned up once out of sight. The temperature of '''Level 434''' is typically 59 degrees Fahrenheit (15 degrees Celsius) but can drop to 43 degrees Fahrenheit (6.11 degrees Celsius) during nighttime hours.

'''Level 434''' possess a day-night cycle of 12 hours, with 7 hours of daytime and 5 hours of nighttime. This cycle is not affected no matter what time one enters the level at. Sunset and sunrise, instead of being a slow, gradual fade similar to the [[The Frontrooms|Frontrooms]], happens very quickly, with sunrise lasting 5 minutes and sunset lasting 7 minutes. Upon the commencement of nighttime, all lights will turn on one by one, including the level's houses, casting an orange-yellow light through the windows. 

A multitude of silhouettes also appear within the windows, giving the appearance of each house being occupied, although entering a house proves this to not be the case. At first, these figures will appear to be partaking in typical activities, such as watching TV, cooking, and playing board games. However, after a certain amount of time, each figure will stop their activities, and turn towards the window, before freezing in place. They will continue to remain in a state of stasis until eventually fading away by sunrise. Cases of shadows being frozen in uncanny positions have been reported, including hanging upright on the ceiling and being twisted in unnatural knots. It is currently unknown if the figures are an actual entity or a profound effect created by the level.
{{Blurimage|file=Screenshot 2025-04-04 082038-434-2-1.png|caption=Another image of '''Level 434'''.}}
Despite the exterior setup of the level's houses being profoundly different, entering any house within '''Level 434''' brings one to the same exact interior setup, with the same architectural layout, similar furniture, and similar aesthetics. Foodstuffs are stored within cupboards and fridges, and upon taking an item, a new, identical version appears within the cabinet via unknown means. The food itself has been described as "tasteless but addicting". At the second floor of each house is two identical bedrooms; one being a master bedroom with an affixed bathroom, and the other being a smaller room with a crib. One of the few differences between each house lies within this smaller room, as the wallpaper is either in a shade of blue or pink, seemingly indicating a boy or girl's room.

'''Level 434''' is almost completely silent, with no wind, no bird chirp, and no naturally occurring sounds to speak of. The only noise that can be generated within '''Level 434''' are noises caused by one's body movements, such as speaking, walking, and breathing. No sound is made when one interacts with objects, as the doors have no squeak, throwing something onto the ground produces vibrations but no soundwaves, and running water cannot be heard. The absence of most sounds within '''Level 434''' would usually lead one to insanity after a certain period of time, however, this is negated by the '''Homeowner Effect'''.
{{Blurimage|file=YonderSuburbia.png|caption=A third image of '''Level 434''', with the houses being a more neutral color.}}
Brochures and flyers can be found in random areas throughout '''Level 434''' functioning as an overview to the level itself. The level, referred to as "Yonder", is described as being "the perfect place to raise a family" by the flyers. Each brochure also contains overviews and pictures of the level taken via unknown means, as well pictures containing smiling individuals, which invokes a strong uncanny valley feeling upon first glance. 

Paintings can also be found within the interior of houses within '''Level 434''', which change at the start of each day. Usually, each painting shows natural landscapes or a specific house with the level. However, photos similar to the ones present with the level's advertisement flyers also have a chance to be displayed on paintings within houses, though unlike the brochure pictures, these pictures feature black sockets in place of eyes, and a wide, unnatural grin in a vantablack hue. At the bottom of each photo is the words "You'll never have to worry about home again!" written in a style similar to an artist's signature in black ink.
==The Homeowner Effect==
{{Phenomenon Class||frequency=4|effectiveness=5|danger=5|width=}}
The '''Homeowner Effect''' is an anomalous phenomenon specific to '''Level 434''', and manifests immediately upon entering the level, increasing in severity the longer one stays within '''Level 434'''. There is currently no cure to the phenomenon other than leaving the level, where the effects are capable of going away slowly depending on how long one was on '''Level 434''', otherwise the effects are permanent.

There are 5 stages to the '''Homeowner Effect''':

===Stage 1===
Stage 1 begins immediately after entering '''Level 434'''. No changes are noticeable in the first 15 minutes after entering the level. However, as Stage 1 progresses, one will begin to feel a sense of attachment to the level itself, despite its lifeless nature. At this stage, one is capable of delaying the later stages by remaining aware of the level's nature, however, being aware will not cure the effect completely, and sooner or later, one will fall into the second stage of the phenomenon.

Stage 1 begins upon entry.
===Stage 2===
Within Stage 2, one will slowly become one with the level's lifeless nature. One's feelings will slowly begin to disappear, starting within the legs. Pain responses are usually the first to be target within this stage, followed by the main senses of touch, smell, and taste. One's movements will be erratic, similar to a wounded animal, and calculated, similar to a robot. One is able to cure the '''Homeowner Effect''' at this stage by leaving the level, but remaining aware will not delay the phenomenon.

Stage 2 begins 30 minutes to 2 hours after entry.
===Stage 3===
Stage 3 involves one becoming more number, with the numbness spreading to one's entire body. At this stage, it is recommended to find egress as soon as possible, as this is the final stage where one is able to recover from the '''Homeowner Effect'''. Once Stage 3 is over, there is no turning back, and one will be afflicted permanently from the phenomenon, even if they exit the level.

Stage 3 begins 4 to 5 hours after entry.
===Stage 4===
Stage 4 is marked by plaguing headaches and repeated loss of consciousness thereafter. The feelings of attachment one has towards the level will temporarily subside, replaced by awareness about finding egress. At this stage, one cannot rid themselves of the '''Homeowner Effect'''.

Stage 4 begins 8 to 9 hours after entry.
===Stage 5===
Stage 5 is where most individuals stop at during the '''Homeowner Effect'''. During this stage, one's awareness and mental stage begins to corrode, creating an effect similar to Alzimer's, trapping one in blissful ignorance. One will begin to experience thoughts of staying on '''Level 434''' despite dangers and making the level their new home. As Stage 5 progresses, one will begin to forget about the entirety of the Backrooms and their [[The Frontrooms|home]], with their only known reality being their new prison.

Stage 5 begins 1 to 2 days after entry.
==Entities==
===The Eyeless Ones===
'''The Eyeless Ones''' are the only known entities within '''Level 434'''. Upon first glance, '''The Eyeless Ones''' appear similar to an average human; however, they possess pitch black sockets in place of eyes, and a wide grin curved into an unnatural angle, also in a pitch-black hue, similar to the portraits that can appear within '''Level 434'''. '''The Eyeless Ones''' are typically seen wandering the streets within '''Level 434''', although can also be found within houses as well. Upon encountering a wanderer, '''The Eyeless Ones''' will offer to show them around the level, however, trusting any of them will only lead one deeper into the level, where they will be farther away from any exits and be susceptible to the '''Homeowner Effect'''. Due to the heavily expansive nature of '''Level 434''', encountering an '''Eyeless One''' is uncommon, with 1 out of 10 individuals encountering an instance and 1 out of 100 encountering two separate instances whilst on the level.

===''The Level Itself?''===
Though it is widely unconfirmed, it is theorized that '''Level 434''' is an entity itself due to the level's seemingly predatory behaviors towards individuals and the level's influence outside of itself, manifesting as [[Backchat (Collaborative Log)|Backchat]] posts, flyers within various levels, and the '''Level 9.12 Incident''', in which the level's former page was deleted in an unknown fashion. This theory is still being investigated and no new evidence supporting this facet has been discovered.
==Entrances and Exits==
===Entrances===
Most of '''Level 434's''' entrances are in a state of spatial flux and shift from level to level. The main way of telling whether one is entering '''Level 434''' is the presence of any nearby sign saying the word Yonder, such as a hotel room sign or a road work sign. Walking in specific doors or walking into areas indicated by Yonder signs leads one to '''Level 434'''.
===Exits===
*Entering a house with the address "711" will bring one to [[Level 711]].
*On occasion, an out of place parked car can be found, with the key in the ignition. Entering the car and driving it will lead one to [[Level 178]] after a period of time.
*Entering a house adorned with oriental decorations leads one to [[Level 437]] or [[Level 909]].
*Noclipping through a tree has a chance to take one to [[Level 427]].
*Typing "LVL 435.TRANSPORT" on any terminal in this level will transport one to [[Level 435]]. Alternatively, one could try finding a door labeled "435" walking through that door will also lead to Level 435

